SIMPLE: oiled
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: oiled
<hw>oiled</hw> <pr>(oild)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered
or treated with oil; dressed with, or soaked in, oil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Drunk; inebriated.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oiled silk</b></col>, <cd>silk rendered waterproof by
saturation with boiled oil.</cd> -- <col><b>well oiled</b></col>,
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>operating smoothly and efficiently.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd>
<cd>very drink.</cd> <mark>[slang]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oiler</ent>⟦br⟧
